statement_latex:
Show, without using the explicit prime factorization of 1729, but using
the following congruences instead, that 1729 is composite.

\begin{align*}
2^{18} &\equiv 1065 \mod{1729} \\
2^{36} &\equiv 1 \mod{1729}
\end{align*}

statement_raw:
